    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Activity 1.1: Capacity building of selected local civil society organizations (CSOs) and local government on GBV victims’ data collection and safely storage.Activity 1.2: Capacity building of media, service providers, CSOs and community leaders to empower women and girls.Activity 1.3: Capacity building of community health workers on psychosocial and mental health.Activity 2.1: Develop IEC materials, document and disseminate stories for gender empowerment to reduce GBV at the community level.Activity 2.2: Hardware support to strengthen access to justice service for women and girls.Activity 2.3: Conduct gender and entrepreneurship empowerment to women suffered from GBV.Activity 2.4: Provide psychosocial counseling and health support to GBV survivors and their families.Activity 3.1: Establish and strengthen Municipality Citizens Network for justice (MCNJ).Activity 3.2: Establish linkages with existing resources to improve the livelihood opportunities for GBV victims.Activity 3.3: Develop and implement joint action plans among the local government CSOs and community using the CSC approach to enhance mutual accountability and improve service delivery.Activity 3.4: Collaborative dialogues and meeting among elected/political representatives (women, Dalit and marginalized) and JSPs at provincial level and federal level to improve service delivery."
      },
      "ne": null
    },
